  </h3>
<p>Given the full path to a folder, returns a list of all Folders in the path
hierarchy, starting at the root folder, and ending at the requested folder.
The given path is relative to the context's root folder and does not
include the root folder's name (e.g., âcourse filesâ). If an empty path
is given, the context's root folder alone is returned. Otherwise, if no
folder exists with the given full path, a Not Found error is returned.</p>
